commit.title: Fix LatchedChannelSource to maintain ordering; bump minor version (interface of same changed)
util-core to 5.3.11; match netty version to finagle; reimplement LatchedChannelSource with Offer/Broker
convert MemcacheCodec to use ByteBuffer internally
disallow using a singleton fas a signal. add test.
allow a stream to be closed inline, to avoid races.
at least a little bit of docs
don't close a channel until it has a receiver.
simplify: make Stream just be another signal that can be added to an outbound message.
next go-round: codify the latching mechanism into LatchedChannelSource, and use a CodecControl object to let the encoder start streaming.
golfing: give the encoder a lazy-created channel source for dumping stream data into.

change the streaming encoder so that future messages are encoded directly and injected right after the codec. it upsets finagle if messages are injected back at the top. also, when we decide there's nothing to send, trigger the future on the eaten message, so finagle will know it's done.
add support for a returned stream in memcache responses (for kestrel).
turn Encoder from a partial function to a real trait, which gets a copy of its netty channel for later streaming.
explicit typing for some methods, in case that makes intellij less cranky. (nope.)
add Signalling mixin, and a test.
fix written-bytes count and add a test for it
move to 2.1.0 because ostrich/actor support was dropped
remove ostrich dependency, and add idea support
Updated ostrich dependency to 3.0.4 (3.0.0-SNAPSHOT not found on maven.twttr.com).  Resolves sbt package-dist failure.
apparently this version refers to the version of scala that sbt uses.
rename Decoder to Codec and make it do encoding too.
Updated dependencies to Scala 2.8.1 and Specs 1.6.6
make Decoder be explicitly stateful. it depends on FrameDecoder which is already stateful so you can't really put that egg back together again.
fix twitterActors dependency so it will work with scala 2.8. :/
disable cross-paths again, and use a newer netty.
scalac is confused by this annotation. apparently it's doc-only tho.
use newer twitter-actors with shutdown bug fix.
catch exceptions in the decoder and reset the state machine before re-throwing.
make this a snapshot. use twitter actors.
MemcacheRequest: return the number of bytes read.
add HttpRequest demo. and it works! :)
add the 2 convenience methods for readLine.
add Decoder and a starter test.
remove unused Done state. make it easier for a stage to return another stage. add readLine.
